Algorithm Description:
    MY PROGRAM DOES NOT USE DIFFERENT ALGORITHMS DEPENDING ON PARAMETER SIZE
    In fact I only used the random library but felt like I should include a description 
    because I was unclear whether I still needed one regardless of whether I used different 
    algorithms. I have  implemented the same algorithm as we covered in class. 
    I used the miller rabin algorithm to check if a random int from 1 to 
    (2^numbits) -1 is prime. I use this to get two prime integers p and q. I set e = (2^16) + 1. 
    I then find the modular inverse of e mod N where N= p*q. I do this using 
    the extended euclidean algorithm I implemented based off of the lecture.
    This value mod phi(N) is eqaul to d.
